name: Augustiner-Keller
description: Historisches Restaurant mit großem Biergarten & Bierstüberl, das bayerische & internationale Speisen anbietet.

reviews.comment:
An excellent place to try some traditional German food! We ate outside and it was really fresh. As for the dishes, they were tasty and huge enough; I tried the duck and it was very very tender.
The staff was attentive and the prices were fair enough.
I highly recommend this restaurant.

Great beer.
Massive beer garden.
If you like German food...I'm sure this stuff would be up your street. Vegans need not apply. Lots of people had their own picnics.
Cash only.

One of the biggest beer garden in Munich.. full of life, sounds, great beer of course and a large selection of traditional German food to beat. Brilliant for a sunny day out with family and friends.. loved it.

Had a chance to try the crispy pork hock and, as a huge fan of pork fat and skin, I was not disappointed. It was only a half one, but still a big portion to me that I had to share it with my friend. The potato salad was also very good.

This place is great because the beer is really good and it's fun to sit in the garden and drink/eat. The food is awesome. I feel very relaxed here however I am also very bias to this beer garden because it was the first I went to when I arrived in Germany, fell in love with it, and never felt the need to go anywhere different. Even though it's in the middle of the city, it feels like it's tucked away. There's also a substantial playground for the young'ins!

name: Hofbräuhaus München
description: Brauhaus aus dem 16. Jahrhundert über 3 Ebenen, mit bayerischem Restaurant, Shows & guter Stimmung.

reviews.comment:
We thoroughly enjoyed our time here. Try your best to sit in the courtyard! The pretzel 🥨 and beer 🍺 were fantastic and the food was just okay.

Don’t be too hard on them, I can’t imagine how difficult it would be to keep all of this food ready to go.

Always ask for a seasonal menu and try the seasonal beer! The restrooms are very nice.

Put a napkin over your nice clothes if you are eating a dish with gravy!

Definitely worth a visit to experience the craziness of a beer hall, the 1L beer jugs and huge full pork knuckle!!! You might be lucky enough to see locals who dress up in traditional Bavarian attire while dining too!!
Just keep in mind, it does get super busy and if you’re in a group of less than 4 people, you could be sharing a table with others (which is a great way to make new friends!).

Phenomenal atmosphere with lively German music and plenty of beer options to go around. The place is huge so it's very easy to find seating and the food is good. If you come here, you're coming for the beer so definitely order the 1L beers and enjoy the German atmosphere.

This restaurant has a nice yard which allows people to eat outside with peace! We liked the food but it was a little expensive. The beer was really good! The staff was not always kind and confusing to us. For a quick locally brewed beer this place is really good!

AMAZING atmosphere. You have to visit this place when you come to visit Munich. Such a characterful place. So much happiness and fun. It's a real joy to dine here. Everybody is happy. At times there is a German band playing classic folklore music. Food is great. I would really recommend going for the traditional dishes. And also not that expensive. A must on your to-do list while visiting Munich.

name: Prinz Myshkin
description: Vegetarisches Edelrestaurant mit minimalistischer, moderner Deko & Fokus auf kreativer internationaler Küche.

reviews.comment:
Nice atmosphere, tasty vegan options and good service. Really busy in the weekends so I'd recommend to book.

I am updating my review, it was previously 5 stars but I was there last week again and the food was terrible. Everything tasted like if it was reheated in the microwave.
Good place for purely vegetarian food, nice ambience, friendly service. The food is good, but expect downtown pricing. An institution in Munich.
Food was excellent, very creative and a wide variety. I will definitely come again next time I’m in Munich!

I love this restaurant. I went with my daughter and enjoyed it so much we went back the next night. Great choice on the menu and we asked one of the staff for her opinion. Anna kindly recommended some dishes and wine which were just amazing and she looked after us brilliantly on both nights. We will definitely be visiting again!
Excellent meal. Service was great, very good variety of dishes on the menu.

name: Kilians Irish Pub
description: Regionale und internationale Biere, Pubgerichte, Livemusikabende und Sport-TV in einem angesagten Lokal.

reviews.comment: My favourite pub in Munich. Good beers good vibes and the people are so kind there. The food is delicious I love the soups which are changing every week. Barkeepers are just amazing people. Love them all. Live music and karaoke also began again😍 every week they have a special menu which is amazing😍 just go, have a beer, listen to the music and eat delicious food❤️

This is a great Irish pub. Live music, good bar staff, tasty beverages, and a great atmosphere where you can relax, have fun and not feel bad for speaking English. The food is standard bar fair but you don't go here for that, it's just a fun welcoming place to have a few beers and enjoy friends.

It is a cool place to go for a beers with the friends. They food is what you would expect from a pub (fried food, hamburgers etc) so it fits to eat something while drinking some beers. Some days they also have live music or karaoke night. The area is exactly the city center so it is also perfect to go there after hanging around or doing some tourism in Munich. However, since it is in the center, i recommend to make a reservation

Good place to have beer with snacks. Service is good and the place has a nice vibe to it. Liked the music n ambience here. Food and drink options are plenty n is not very expensive. Just one problem the food portion is quite high for one person. Overall good experience
The best bar in Munich. Friendly Staff and Live music. All Beers are perfect. Just go there on Thursday or Friday on Saturday is too crowded. And we will meet there for sure 🤣👌💪

name: Spatenhaus at the opera
description: Rustikales Restaurant für bayerische Gerichte, selbstgebrautes Bier und eleganter Speiseraum in oberer Etage.

reviews.comment:
Good beer, nice vibe, good for business, friends and even family.
Food is good, typical Bavarian dishes.
Diligent and kind staff
Great food, very professional service. From Bavarian basics to delicate dishes: a real pleasure for the taste buds... And the Spaten beer is great, too 🍺

It used to be better. Just very expensive with much less quality. Germans are still served first and foremost even if they order a soup. You, tourist and non-german will wait forever for a fillet that you will pay 36euros. Unprofessional, unreliable. A last choice if other places are closed.
We had a very nice experience. You can enjoy very tasty Bavarian food in this central location.

This place was perfectly average for a tourist location in Europe. Took to long to get service. The food was so so. And it all cost a bit to much.  Honestly go down a few blocks to the open air market and get some street food. It’s cheaper and will taste better. This place just has the luxury of a good location. If it wasn’t for that it wouldn’t be in business anymore. Not worth your precious vacation meals.

name: Brenner Opengrill
description: Italienische Speisen in imposanter Halle mit Marmorsäulen und modernem Dekor, durchgängige Küche & Bar.

reviews.comment: Phenomenal place with great staff! Phone is amazing but a little on the pricey side. Look for a good time with family and friends, this would be the place. Gets busy for quick
Electric atmosphere. The restaurant was huge and cavernous. We were lucky to get a walk-in table. People watching alone was enjoyable. The menu is simple but delicious.

Food was really good but the service was terrible. I had to wait 30min for someone to come to take my order, and it was after I asked one of the waiters that I wanted to order. The terrace outside is beautiful and the ambience is nice.
Super restaurant! The food was delicious and the vibe was great. One of the best steaks I’ve ever had.
5 star to service staff. Quick and courteous. Ambience, crowd and food good but not exceptional.

name: Wirtshaus Zum Straubinger
description: Traditionelles bayerisches Wirtshaus & Biergarten mit gemütlicher Holzvertäfelung und regionalen Gerichten.

reviews.comment: Food was tasty but not the best German I had. The knuckle was really heavy and probably not so well cooked since I was not very well the day after. Waiters are nicer than average though. Ok place.

Food was good, but small portion. Price is okay for quality but high for the amount of food served. The waiter was a bit overwhelmed - too few waiters were deployed in the central area of the outside garden. The outdoor area is really beautiful with the trees and there is enough shadow. Sadly the place was not very clean (table, seats, restroom) in our last visit. I hope that improves.
The most amazing schweinshaxe. A must try when in Munich. Also always ask for Stephen, he is the kindest and most amazing waiter in the whole world.
If you get the chance to visit Munich and are a meat eater, you must try the Straubi Schnitzel. I will definitely return here just to experience it over and over again.
Great service, good beer, pork knuckle was a good sized portion although a little dry.

name: Cafe Kranich
description: Café mit pfiffigem Ambiente & großer Terrasse, das deutsche & internationale Gerichte und Sandwiches anbietet.

reviews.comment: Loves this place and the vibe. Not huge fan of any music with lyrics (i know!) but this place is super cool. And the staff, best in the town. Bar was super busy and the staff were chilled and having fun :)

I had a good experience the first time that I had brunch here, so I returned because I also liked its interior design. It was not a good decision. Instead of fresh orange juice they brought us packaged ones. Their excuse was that they ran out of fresh orange juice, however, nobody mentioned that when we ordered. In general, the experience was quite disappointing. Definitely not a reliable place to return again.
Very nice place and kind service. Food war great and prices decent. Definitly coming again.
Great for a drink! Cool music and a nice bar ! ( food is average though)
Very good restaurant to eat: raviolis, carpaccio, salad and burguer. And very good beer. The waitress is very nice

name: Zum Franziskaner
description: Bayerisches, familiengeführtes Restaurant, lokale Wurstspezialitäten, mit formellen & rustikalen Speiseräumen.

reviews.comment:
I have been years ago and was excellent, this time the experience was just above fair.
One of my friends is allergic to strawberries and we asked explicitly to have the dessert without it. Well... The vanilla mousse had no sliced strawberries on the side but was covered with strawberry sauce...
We looked for the waiter to complain bit he was outside smoking a cigarette, since the place was nearly empty.

Hope it will be better next time
I've come here a few times. And everything is amazing!! I had the "butchers selection" from the menu. Simply amazin!! Totally recommend!
If you are looking for a truly Bavarian experience this is the place! The restaurant is huge yet very well organised so you still have the feeling you are in a normal sized place. Food was very good!
Very rude waiters!!! Made us wait for 30 minutes and not even looking at us, we left without eating
This is a wonderful restaurant, great food ,great staff!

name: L'Osteria
description: Bekanntes italienisches Restaurant in München. 1999 in Italien gegründet und seitdem international geführt.

reviews.comment: If you want to own a restaurant as business choose this one. It’s unbelievable busy. Full of guests and long line waiting at the door. From gastronomic point of view it is not good at all. Something like a fast food Italian. You get this quality at petrol stations in Italy. Wine is very week and wine list very short not representing Italy at all. Mainly young people hanging around. Of course the house is beautiful.

Beautiful place to dine in. Food was really good too. The prawn spaghetti I had was really good and flavourful. The pizza was huge and decent, but I hope they can cut it into slices first before serve it to the table. Caprese was fresh and yummy. Service was okay. Overall it was a lovely experience

- Very nice dishes and flavors (we ate pizza, pasta, salad and desert).
- Very nice interior/decoration.
- Relatively reasonable prices (for Munich restaurant standards).
- Be aware that this restaurant can be very crowded.
- Specific employees are rude (most though are friendly and polite).
- Tables were not cleaned very well (oil stains were visible).

Went here with the team during lunch! I really liked the spinach/egg pizza it was very tasty and also the portion was enough. The only downside is that it took a little too much to get our order, pizzas should come much much faster.

Very cool vibe and good and large pizza. However the service was lacking, the waitress was very short with us and when wanting to order more drinks it took over 20 minutes before she would even acknowledge us. It was only a Tuesday so I can imagine it being even worse on a crowded night.

name: Schneider Bräuhaus München
description: Restaurant, das von einer renommierten Weißbierbrauerei betrieben wird, mit zahlreichen klassischen Gerichten.

reviews.comment: Lovely beers, did not try the food, but it looked delicious. Excellent atmosphere. The staff was friendly and accommodating non-German speakers. Also dog friendly.
Great service, great prices, and great food. The beer is tasty and plentiful. We had breakfast and dinner there, and we will definitely stop there on our next visit to Munich

Good food with also seasonal menu. Best weissbier selection from tap. We liked both the original, tap4 with hop taste and tap5 a lighter version. Also nice service with kind waiters. Only missing thing was a wiener schnitzel from veal.
Incredible. If you want the full Bavarian experience come here. Very high quality food. Most excellent and not expensive

Old, but renovated place with a lot of space inside and a small restaurant garden, still often crowded. Fast and nice service speaking English. A large variety of foods and beers available - tasty and not that pricy for the location.

name: Augustiner am Platzl
description: Restaurant, das von einer renommierten Münchner Brauerei betrieben wird, mit zahlreichen klassischen Gerichten.

reviews.comment: Our experience was one of unfriendly service and being forced into paying as much as possible. Best example: Even though we ordered a salad without cheese (with cheese was 5€ extra), the waiter shuffled a salad WITH cheese under our noses, briefly stating that “the kitchen wouldn’t allow to sell salads without cheese. Then maybe don’t put it on your menu. In essence: If you don’t want to be treated like an inhuman commercial money tree, don’t go here.

This is my first time in EU and my last day in Munich to have dinner before flying back.

The food is great. The potato tastes delicious and native. The pork elbow is awesome.

Just one feeling, that the waiter is less friendly or proactive. Not sure why... Probably because I were speaking English rather than Germany?

Overall, the quality of food is good to have a try after hanging around Marienplatz

Tourist trap.  So many great choices - skip the dry pork knuckle and indifferent service.   Go elsewhere.   Narrow sidewalk seating means you get to share your meal with every passerby.   Waiter made sure we knew tips were not excluded but omitted they were discretionary.   Beer was half froth but at least cold.

we were in the restaurant today, it's super great, we felt very well looked after with the multilingual service staff, thank you very much for the nice atmosphere we give 5 stars. and we will continue to recommend it.
thank you thank you again

Absolutely will not visit this place again. Rude staff who speak condescendingly and treat you like dirt. Acknowledges your additional order of water with a look of disdain, turn and walk away when you are speaking to them halfway as if you are nothing. Totally appalling.. for crying out loud, the food is not even worth a 2.5 out of 5. Never ever again… be warned!

name: Gaststätte FAUN
description: Bistroähnliches Restaurant mit klassischem Ambiente, internationale & deutsche Gerichte und Augustiner-Bier.

reviews.comment: The best Club Sandwich I have eaten in my life! The ingredients are fresh and the food really tasty as well as the service: definitely top five in München and coming back again
Delicius Bavarian food, nice attention and kind staff.

Great bar/restaurant with Augustiner beer and yummy food. However, the management should think about an Adult-only rule on weekends from 17:00 for a less stressful experience, so adults can enjoy the atmosphere without kids screaming and running around between the aisles being a potential hazard for the waiters and guests.
Super nice food and great wait staff - amazing schnitzel
Super value lunch menu friendly staff good location

name: Café Luitpold
description: Modernes Kaffeehaus in prunkvollem Gebäude aus dem 19. Jh., spezialisiert auf Kuchen & Gourmetschokoladen.

reviews.comment: Very nice place for a wonderful breakfast. The terrace is sunny and you can enjoy delicious breakfast. The Benedict eggs are delicious. We don't test the patisserie but they look delicious.

Great place, great location and exceptional traditional cafe. Prices are at the upper end. Service is professional and friendly. The selection of cake is great. We enjoyed their huge 500 ml Ice-cream coffee.

Love the ambiance of the inner garden. We always come here for Kaiserschmarrn very delicious and the portions are good for 2 people. The advice for the desert is to add a one scoop of vanilla ice-cream on top of it.

I was a bit scared at first as you are completely ignored when you wait for a table. But once you sit, the service is quite efficient! The lady was nice and quick. The cakes were really good but the drinks were only okay. However, I also bought some things from their shop and I wasn't disappointed. The chocolate was very good!

Beware of a truffle chocolate cake! Purchased it for a colleague’s birthday, next day in the office a very unpleasant surprise was found inside it.

REPLY: the fluffy MOLD was found inside. The cake was replaced afterwards with different one but imagine the situation when you are in a office and in front of all your colleagues to experience this 'WOW' moment.

Also, there was no sticker with a date when a cake was made or best before,  so I don’t understand this complete lack of food and sanitary standards!

name: Sushi+Soul
description: Großes japanisches Restaurant und Bar mit stylisher, minimalistischer Einrichtung, Whisky- und Rumverkostung.

reviews.comment: The place is easy to reach, friendly staff. Food was good, but not something so extraordinary. For the set that cost about 45 euro kinda expected bigger portion(in menu was written that its for 2 persons). And tables are too small to fit everything for 2 people.
One of the best sushi restaurants in Munich, ordered so many pieces of sushi which came out on a huge wooden boat and the ambience at this place is top! Would definitely come here again.

One of my new favorite places in Munich! I’ve been wanting to go for a long time - it is amazing! Tons of options, cocktails half price after 11pm (Sun-Thurs) and sushi half price after 10pm (also Sun-Thurs). Everything is super fresh and really tasty! Very good service and a great vibe. We have zero complaints and loved every single thing we ordered! 😍 Our favorites were the tempura, anything with yellowtail or scallops, and the cocktails!
Beautiful sushi place in a quiet neighbourhood. The food was great and the staff was very helpful and professional. Oh and the sushi was great as well!
The right place for a date or getting together with friends. Plenty of drink options, specially cocktais. Sushi was very good.

name: Vapiano
description: Knusprig-fluffige Pinsa, frische & hausgemachte Pasta, knackige Insalate und köstliche Dolci – das alles kannst Du entspannt unterm Olivenbaum genießen. Wir von VAPIANO bereiten alles frisch, vor Deinen Augen und nach Deinen Wünschen zu.

reviews.comment: Ver nice restaurant. They have a very unique system and the prices are affordable. Now I mentioned the system. First you get a card and buy everything you want then after you are finished you give them the card and pay. It's an Italian restaurant with lots of dishes and they have good drinks and an extra bar for them. I recommend the ice tea. It's the perfect place to go with friends or family. I liked it there very much and I would go there again soon.
Google said it was open on maps but it wasn't

Great ambiance. It has a fancy feel to it but also very easy going. Loved the concept of ordering food and then sitting at a table of choice. Paying only when leaving the restaurant and you can easily tip using the touchscreen at the end.
The food was great as well. Can totally recommend.
Great place for pizza, pasta. I personally like the outdoor terrace sitting area. Great vibes, stay as long as you want.
Best location, good service but come on people! Get it together. The pasta was undercooked and in clumps, the salad was old and limp! Where’s the manager? Call me!

name: Park Café
description: An unserer gut sortierten Bar finden Sie nicht nur hervorragende Weine, internationale Top-Spirituosen, zapffrische Bierspezialitäten vom Hofbräu München, sondern auch die feinen Röstungen von Julius Meinl aus Wien aus der italienischen Storm-Barista-Kaffeemaschine.

reviews.comment: We've been there for Sunday jazz brunch. The food was amazing, many choices between usual breakfast and lunch, different kinds of fish, meat and vegetables/fruits. I only missed some more kinds of cheese

Cool beer garden location in the center of Munich.
Great food selection. Service was a bit slow but it was also crowded. So completely justified.
Bigger parties shall reserve a table ahead of time, especially during nice warm summer days

Good food for fair prices and great cocktails BUT the service could be much better and they only accept cash.
What is wrong with them? Wake up to the 21st century

We went there for the brunch. Big Plus was that we got a great table without reservation. The food was good, unfortunately it took me quite some time to get plain yoghurt which was unfortunately forgotten but in the end I was successful. The food was great and more then enough. Waitress and everyone super friendly.
I really like the atmosphere at dusk. Good service. Great menu variety. Note the Grilled Cesar salad doesn't have chicken in it unless requested ;)

name: Ratskeller München
description: Traditionelles deutsches Restaurant im Herzen von München

reviews.comment: I've travelled a lot and visited many restaurants. This is where you find the most tender tasteful delicious Wiener Schnitzel. Even in the best places in Austria you won't find this quality. Highly recommended! Friendliness depends on the waiter you get. I highly recommend Angelo - he is the best!
Absolutely excellent food. Mid range prices for the very centre of Munich. Lovely chicken. Great deserts. Very nice pasta with cheese. Staff attentive and very pleasant. I recommend.

This is the place to taste typical Bavarian cuisine!
Dark and warm ambience, right at the heart of the city! Professional service and good quality of food!
Don’t miss it if you want a taste of Bavarian food...

Beautiful location. The food was really good too.

What I feel could be improved is service promptness. It wasn't terrible and the place was full so they have the benefit of the doubt 🧐.

We absolutely LOVED this spot. Funny because as we walked in, it wasn't nearly as lively as the places near by, but as the night moved on, the music picked up the clientele, and it felt more celebratory.

Food wise, it serves GREAT Bavarian dishes..   the lamb sausage was a first for me. The pork belly was wonderful as well. But the tops was the Black Forest Cake and the wine. Enjoy a nice date, or a large family dinner!

name: Restaurant Pfistermühle
description: Das Restaurant im Zentrum von München, das Handwerkskunst, Leidenschaft und Echtheit miteinander vereint.

reviews.comment: Hotel restaurant. High quality food and not cheap. I had lamb three ways which was fantastic. They serve a local Ayling lager and it is interesting how many people buy beer! It is a proper Munich thing!  They serve beautiful local bread as a starter which wound up having more because it was so good!!

We had an amazing evening! The service was very friendly, always happy to provide some tips or interesting information about the food. The duck breast was unforgettable!  Thank you, Pfistermühle team!

Visited Munich for the first time, and lucked into finding this restaurant.  It is a wonderful place for a date night!  The staff is super friendly.  They recommendations for dining, and a wine were superb!  I think my favorite dish was the truffled potato soup.  My wife really enjoyed the Turbot in Gin Stain.  You cannot go wrong with either the duck, or the pumpkin cream cheese ravioli.  For dessert try the blueberry cheesecake! Hopefully we will be back to Munich soon, because I want to eat here again!
Absolute favourite! Would definitely keep going back. Love the lunch menu. Very good hospitality.

Returned again after first visit in 2018 and they didn’t disappoint. Super friendly staff completes the experience. The tasting menu was delicious. Awesome find during a trip to Munich. Everything we ordered was delicious. Tasty and beautifully crafted dessert too!

name: Zur Schwalbe
description: Deutsches Restaurant mit südtirolerischen Ausprägung

reviews.comment: Zur Schwalbe is a great hole in the wall Bavarian restaurant with great beer and wonderful atmosphere. The owners and servers are friendly as are the customers. The little bowling lane is a fun little twist you can reserve for parties. I hope to try it some day. Definitely worth a visit.
Wonderful place, very kind personnel, good food, great beers, of course I recommend 🥰

The inner courtyard is like a oasis in the inner city, quite, no traffic. A very nice smaller menu with excellent dishes for fair and adequate prices offers all you need, no matter if you are hungry or just appease one`s appetite. It is also the perfect place to just have a few drinks with friends. The hosts and service are doing a great job not only during these tough times. "Zur Schwalbe" is becoming a home apart from home. Coming back soon.

We had reserved the Kegelbahn and whole experience was good! The food & the service were also nice! The only significant thing that I noticed was the lack of options for vegetarians/vegans (one dish, linsen suppe on the menu which was good).
Nice little gem hidden among buildings. It feels like stepping into a different place once entering. Nice tasty Augustiner beer

name: Kennedy's Bar and Restaurant
description: Welcome to Kennedy’s – where Bavarian lifestyle meets Irish hospitality.

reviews.comment:
I’ve been to this pub many times since 2018, and today was the first time that I had the horrible experience of not being able to enter. There were 2 guys controlling the entrance, a security guy and the “chef (as the security guy called him). The “chef was extremely rude and disrespectful to me. My husband was already there with a friend, keeping a table for 3 people and just waiting for me to join. I explained it, but the “chef didn’t give me enough attention, and no explanations why I couldn’t go in. I was trying my best to speak a broken German, which is not great, but is good enough to understand when others speak the language. Even though I was standing there, I could understand them making fun of the fact that I was trying to get into the bar and the “chef had the “power to block my entrance. Disrespectful, rude and ignorant. I don’t suggest anyone to go through experiences like this, and I hope this “chef understands one day that this is what makes people not going back to places. I didn’t ask his name, but I wanted to leave this review here, so other foreigners can be aware about the type of rudeness they might face at this place.

Update to the staff:
I give a negative review, clearly stating that I felt disrespected, and you don’t have the decency to apologize for it. It just highlights how fake the statement “our clients are the heart of our business is, and rather how unprofessional a business can be.
1. I wasn’t disappointed because I had a delayed entry. I was disrespected because I had my entrance blocked for no clear reason and coming from a very rude “chef. My husband and friend were waiting for me in a table for 3 people, with an empty chair, and I wasn’t allowed to enter.
2. For such a multilingual staff, they didn’t seem to make an effort to speak English to me, even though it’s more than clear that I have a broken German.

Very good food, nice Drinks, great atmosphere and music (especially when there is Karaoke ^^) and friendly personal.
Been here on multiple occasions and would definitely recommend.

You should reserve a table though, since it is always quite crowded.

Went there about two weeks ago and had an absolute blast...
thanks to Luis ...
We went there to have a few quiet drinks but had so much fun that we stayed for ages.
Very good beer and food, nice decorations and easy vibe.
Luis was spot on serving us drinks and some food, made us laugh a lot and gave us a very welcomed feeling even though the pub was very very busy.
All in all i will definitely come back, hopefully when he's on shift.
Cheers for everything !!!
I like the ambience. Cool staff, great hospitality. Food and drinks are superb. Great place to hangout with friends, family and colleagues.

Food here is fantastic and the atmosphere is very lively. However, I had a very miserable encounter with the bartender last night. I was pressured to give tip money (10 cents, but nevertheless) and felt extremely uncomfortable. I've never had such a unnecessary confrontation at any bar or pub in my entire life. I've come to the conclusion that hospitality and good service only exists if you're spending lots of money. If it's something small, be prepared to be either treated poorly or just emotionless.

name: Café am Beethovenplatz
description: An einem schattigen Boulevard zentral in München, in einem denkmalgeschützten Haus aus der Belle Époque befinden sich das „Café am Beethovenplatz“.

reviews.comment: Wonderful restaurant! It was given a great review in Rick Steves travel book. We came 3 times in our 5 day stay in Munich.  Large eclectic menu, there is an English menu if you ask for it. Delicious food, amazing sauces.  Tony plays the piano every evening at 7pm. Best bartender in Munich! Wonderful atmosphere.

When service is so slow that you have to wait one hour to be served with they standard breakfast... that's sad.
Otherways, I like this place and the atmosphere, breakfast menu is inventive and interesting, portions are huge and food is quite good.

We have our regular chess meetups at this cafe every week. Very friendly staff, great live music (piano) and an extremely pleasant ambience. Food and drinks are of course good as well. Highly recommended to visit if you’re in Munich!
Live music, great location, kind staff, a perfect place to sit down and relax.
Stunning place with beautiful live piano music, good wines and cuisine. Absolutely recommend.

name: Wildmosers Restaurant-Cafe am Marienplatz
description: Das Restaurant-Cafe liegt an einem der schönsten und lebendigsten Plätze Münchens: dem Marienplatz

reviews.comment: Wonderful experience! We stopped here on the last night of our trip to Germany as it is conveniently located right next to the Glockenspiel Clock in the city center. The food was rather delicious and our server Frau Richter was very attentive and friendly. We ordered a few beers along with the schnitzel, bratwurst, and fish and chips. My husband has been collecting liter mugs for years and they so kindly let us take one home at no extra cost.

Just a tourist trap in a very good location. In front of the tower and the bell looks like a real Bavarian pub but it’s not. Small inside huge terrace not too good food and very bad wine. Beer might be Ok but have not tried. The good part that it’s open on Sunday when the town is deserted.

we felt very unwelcome. Then it feels like they try to maximize their profit and minimize their costs way too much. The food tasted ok but it looked like so much was missing of what it was on the picture and even some parts of it completely missing. After complaining we got exactly what we complained about specifically but we also said it just doesn’t look like on the picture and they ignored it and kept asking us what we want exactly. I don’t usually complain much but this just ruined our mood and made us feel unwanted and unwelcome. Can’t recommend.

Good food and not too expensive.

Tip is mandatory for those who don't know. One writer was extremely kind while the other one a bit rude

Crowded. The service is slow and not professional. The Egyptian waiter added 6 Euros to the bill, saying it's 10% service  !!! Such a cheap way to steal you.
I payed 71 Euros for 1 pizza and 1 small pasta and salad!!!

name: Augustiner am Dom
description: Traditionelle Deutsche Küche für Jedermann

reviews.comment: Most delicious sausages....very interesting salad and ever best delicious duck 😋 we was in Munich 4 days and eat there every day 😁 the place is on top location and with traditional atmosphere. I like it very much. Thanks guys for this that do.
We were sight seeing and decided to stop by. We had our dog and the first thing our server brought out was a bowl of water for her. The server was fantastic and the food and beer were amazing.

Be aware. If you spend under 15eur you need to pay cash. But there is no sign that tells you this. The waiter was rude and tried to tell us that they can give us a table only if you eat, because everything else is reserved. However, upon looking at the free tables, there was no "Reserved" sign.
Bier was good. Service told us that kitchen was closing at 9:15. We tried to order at 9:05 at we were told kitchen was closed already. Be careful before coming here.

Poor quality food. We wanted to experience the authentic Bavarian food experience. We were warned that it was not the best place to dine in the area, nevertheless we took the chance and it was not good. We enjoyed the experience as a family though. And the traditional Bavarian vibes.

name: Hackerhaus
description: Urige Münchner Wirtshauskultur erleben

reviews.comment: An excellent restaurant when visiting Munich. My husband and I used to eat here when we lived in Munich. The food is always tasty and plentiful. A definite must for a good Bavarian experience in the city. I recommend the Hackerhaus and will visit again when we are back in Munchen.

Nice Bavarian restaurant that has beautiful interiors. We are accommodated without prior reservation. Unfortunately they do not have any chicken items, and I ordered something vegetarian. I didn’t enjoy my food as much as I wanted and my friends were satisfied with their food. However we all had a great time with drinking really good beer and having good conversation. The staff are usual busy while serving, nice while billing attitude which is certainly a part of Bavarian experience.

A lovely beer house and restaurant. We went here as part of our Beer Tour where we had beers (I had a Radler which was less alcohol percentage and tasted more like a shandy) We had meat and cheese platters with pretzels/bread. Super yummy and very generous servings...we couldn't finish it!
Best Spätzle ever! They were so smooth and so so so so good! The salad with the beef strips was phenomenal as well! Will for sure come back!

We sat outside on the pedestrian path which was heated and great!! The Kaiserschmarren was so so good, huge portion, apple sauce and plum sauce and fresh berries on top! The dinner was also very tasty, with quite a few vegetarian /vegan options. We will definitely go back!

name: Arabesk Restaurant
description: Libanesische - Arabische Spezialitäten

reviews.comment:
We had a good dinner experience at Arabesk. We had a voucher which we got as a gift. I recommend to mention this before you order your meal.

We had the Menü and the surprise was this beautiful selection of starters you see in the picture. This was our highlight.

The food was very good and the service as well. We recommend a visit when you like Libanese food. Also we recommend go inside since the interior looks so warm and authentic.
Very good food. We went two times in 1 week as its food is very tasty 😋
Very tasty and good quality food! Service was really good too! We will visit again for sure :)

The appetisers are good and you will enjoy them more than main dishes.
Service is good but not fast .
Price is little bit high around 50€ with main dish and some juice

The way the waiter is dealing with the guests is disrespectful. He thinks he played it smart while he is trying to force you to order something that you don’t want to!!!

I hate this poor way of dealing with guest. The food is good. But manners come before anything.

Behave well!

name: Der Pschorr – das bayerische Wirtshaus am Viktualienmarkt
description: Habt Ihr Lust auf gutes Essen mit nettem Service? Dann kommts vorbei, wir kochen wieder für Euch, schenken ein und sorgen für Euer Wohl und Vertrautheit. Euer Pschorr-Team.

reviews.comment: Pretty good restaurant in the city center. The menu only features regional, seasonal produce and meat! You'll pay a premium for this but the quality and assortment of dishes is suitable for it. The meals are traditional Bavarian, some are the chef's special creations. Staff was very friendly, service fast. Only the steak (Zwiebelrostbraten) seemed to have been made in a hurry with the outside being crispy rather than tender. Otherwise recommended. Interior is a mix of modern and traditional design, can be rather noisy due to the open concept. Reserve ahead because it's usually very busy.

First of all, I want to say that I was having a nice dinner when the waiter comes to us at the end with the bill and then started to push us that we must pay a tip for him because his salary comes from there. I can understand that tips are important to him but we are in Germany not in United States and this kind of behavior from waiter could be quiet intimidatory.

Food was okay and the price “not cheap but also okay.

One of my favourite places to visit for a bier when in Munich.

Listen for the bell to ring to know when a new keg has been tapped. Get one fresh from the wooden barrel.
Large portions and kindness. I have asked to warm up again my dish (as i was busy changing my baby) and the servior brought back me a warm dish to the kitchen. Bravo

Been coming here for years and they have good beer, good food and good service. The location is also great right next to the Viktualienmarkt. Plenty of outdoor seating and the menu is small but great. The haxe here is good as are the beef sausages. The helles from the wood barrel is really excellent and overall a great experience.

name: Wirtshaus in der Au
description: Bier und Knödel seit 1901

reviews.comment: Very nice place. 2thumbs up. The ambiance is much nicer then most “traditional “  Restaurants in Munich. Speedy and friendly Staff. Excellent local Food and a Clever Menu.  Busy Place and frequently used by the locals. also a big plus, ..not so touristy. i’ll recommend to make reservations or call in before hand. Minimum 4 starts. Enjoy!
Lovely traditional German restaurant. Lively atmosphere. Friendly service. Delicious food. I recommend trying the pork roast & their dark beer!

We had breakfast. Scrambled eggs, König Ludwig plate and German pancakes with a mix of berry sauce. It was great! Even a bit much. I can recommend their unique lemonades (raspberry+rhubarb).
The service was fast and friendly. Quality and freshness amazing.
Some fantastic interesting food at a great price. The staff was very helpful with decision making. Very beautiful ambience as well.
This place is excellent. A great example of Bavarian cuisine. Great menu , a very good selection of beers on offer and impeccable service. Highly recommended.

name: Teatro Bar Tapas
description: Das Teatro ist die Bühne für Menschen, die das Leben lieben. Gerne Wein und Tapas genießen. Nette Leute kennen lernen. Plaudern und lachen. Und vor allem: echte Gastfreundschaft zu schätzen wissen. Seit 1998 ist die Tapas-Bar im ehemaligen Theater Drehleier der kulinarische Anziehungspunkt in München Haidhausen.

reviews.comment: Super cozy space. They have a great selection of tapas. For tapas I would say it is for sure the best place in Munich. The interior is also great and the service is motivated and always in a good mood when I went there.
Awesome tapas bar!!! The prices a really fair the drinks are really good and the bread is free. Also the Service is just Perfect!! I recommend the place.
Loved this place. Very busy so need to book (any day).  Good range of food, great atmosphere and friendly service.  Highly recommended.

Extremely overrated.. poor to average quality food. Nothing felt fresh. Roasted vegetables were unpleasantly cold and felt almost a week old. Artichokes felt defrosted. Potatoes were nice but nothing near special. Drinks were nice. Overall bad value for money
Absolutely love the food and ambience! Very cool vibe. Always make sure to reserve in advance!

name: Molly Malones
description: Irish Pub Munich

reviews.comment:
good old irish pub in the middle of munich.

Its always a good evening when i go there!
Great fish & chips. Music not too loud.
Very well priced and excellent food! A very cool little spot!
best guinness in munich. and the fish and chips is very good too.
Nice fish and chips 👍🏻 good vibes 😊

name: Café Zimt
description: In liebevoll renovierter Architektur erwartet Sie ein aufmerksamer und freundlicher Service und eine engagierte, kreative Küchencrew, die Ihnen einen angenehmen Aufenthalt bereiten möchte.

reviews.comment: Cozy place, great food, the best cakes with vegan and gluten-free options, and super friendly staff. The lunch menu varies every day - always fresh, healthy, and delicious, both vegetarian and non-vegetarian. Amazing selection of daily homemade cakes, often with gluten-free or vegan options. And the Zimt Croissant beats any bakery in town. 🥐 New opening hours extended to 10pm, with kitchen open until 8pm.

Love it!!!
Great lunch menu and fast service, so works great for a quick lunch break - picture: salmon with vegetable curry and couscous bowl.
Amazing cakes (and I'm very picky about cakes!), good coffee.
Very uniquely super tasty mulled wine in winter time.
They're super friendly as well.
Super super recommended, one of our favorite places! 😍

Maybe it's not fresh when I visited  at 8:30...But same prices.Not discount.
They are yummy but if you will make  fresh 🥐,you can get five stars.
Very high prices. For take away: 2 pcs of cake + 2 pcs of simple bakery = 13,80 EUR.

Café Zimt is my go to spot for the best Zimt Schneken in the Glockenbachviertal. Service is super friendly and food is good quality. When it is sunny they have plenty of outside area to sit. Indoors is quite spacious for München Cafe‘s as well. Unfortunately there is no WiFi so you can’t do home office there. But overall I always have a good experience.

name: M.C. Müller Burger und Bar
description: Burger & Drinks

reviews.comment:
The best burger I’ve ever had.
The place is nice and cozy with an American style.
The waiters are super kind and in overall the price is awesome!

Deeply, deeply suggested! 🤓

So good and really nice and friendly staff! The speak so good English
The 2 danish vikings
Check out the courtyard which is not visible at first, has a great local vibe.
Nice stuff, delicious food even for vegetarians. 10/10
Too crowded and the seats are not that comfortable. Good service and staff though

name: Trachtenvogl
description: Speisecafé

reviews.comment: Great place for a nice casual evening date/meeting. Small Cafe, with nice cakes and service. Try to book a place to sit beforehand if possible, it can get full even on weekdays.

Service was a bit slow in the beginning. We waited a good 20 minutes at least to get a waiter's attention to get our orders but eventually managed. They have a great outdoor seating that's really nice. There's an extensive hot chocolate menu which is great for autumn. You can choose dark chocolate or white chocolate or hot chocolate with pistachio or salted caramel. I chose the hot chocolate with chilli. It wasn't so spicy but tiny hints of spiciness but still very good hot chocolate.

There are pro and con. And still, as a result I give 5 🌟.
We shared Weißwurst breakfast, small breakfast and big breakfast.
1) we were able to reserve a table for breakfast on a short note via phone on a Saturday morning.
2) it is absolutely necessary to make a reservation.
3) the table was unacceptable small for 2
4) the table was inside as requested and nice to sit.
5) they offered a bigger table outside which was better.
6) there were pillows and throws available
7) service was great and quick.
8) food was tasty and fresh.
9) reasonable selection at acceptable prices.
Perfect Brunch place very close to Isar! Though you need a reservation. So book it in advance. Flat white coffee was amazing here!
Very nice service. Thank you 👋

name: Olé Madrid
description: Wir vom Olé Madrid möchten Sie in München mit mediterraner Lebensfreude willkommen heißen und mit wunderbaren Speisen begeistern.

reviews.comment:
Nice and warm atmosphere, feels very Spanish, OK service.
Food has a touch of German tapas.
At time of writinging, every tapas is 6 EUR, and a single tapas may be a fried sausage, potato salat etc.
Good beer! Wine is fine.

Horrible customer service!!! I booked a table for 5 people as i had some friends coming over for holiday. After we made our way to the venue (paid for ubahn ) we arrived and find out they had cancelled our table 8 minute before the scheduled booking without any reason... they were not sorry for the inconvenience and didn't try to resolve the issue. I will definitely not recommend such place!!! 1 star only because i can't give 0!
Extremely loud noise at the mid night with huge loud speakers, drums, and drunk crowds. After a long day of work I just hope to have some decent sleep. But thanks to you that is very hard to happen!
Very good food but they don’t accept credit cards

Portions were way too big, and it didn’t taste very authentically, very greasy, too. We recently came back from Spain and tapas portions were small there and so we could tell how good a tortilla can be. The plate per person for 4 people could have easily fed 6, but following the waitress recommendation we ordered way too much food. Not recommendable because the very high prices are not worth the quality of the food

name: Paulaner Bräuhaus
description: Hausgebraute Lebenslust… Vitali ist am Hahn!

reviews.comment:
You just need to have a good waiter(hard to find there) and than you experience will be amazing!
But the food and drink are delicious!
Great food and atmosphere. Be sure to visit this establishment the next time you’re in Munich. Highly recommended.
First visit, will return. Tasty food , good friendly service, great beer. Nice building with big light interior.
Fantastic Zwickl beer! Food is excellent too. Quite cozy atmosphere. Highly recommended

Perfect place to go to experience great beers, great wines and great food all in the traditional German way

Great service too

Recommended

name: Hans im Glück
description: Herzlich willkommen bei uns im Birkenwald in München. Genieße unvergleichliche kulinarische Glücksmomente mit Deinen Liebsten in einer entspannten Atmosphäre.

reviews.comment: Great food and service! I didn't speak much German but the staff were very friendly and accommodating. The vegan burger was one of the best I've had

None of the staff members were capable of wearing the mask over their mouth and nose (which is pretty much the only purpose of wearing a mask at all). Even after being specifically asked to do so at our table, the waitress pulled it down again a few minutes later
Very nice burger joint with amazing collection of breads and very good options for vegan, vegetarian, chicken, beef patties... Ambiance is very nice and elegant !
Had a really nice experience. The staff was excellent and the food was amazing.
Great place for burgers! Ambiance very lively and I loved the decor!

name: Hofbräukeller
description: Klassisches bayerisches Restaurant im Neorenaissance-Gebäude mit großem Biergarten & Hofbräuhaus-Bier.

reviews.comment: It's really a good beer garden. The wind the trees and with our friends! Cozy. But the service was ... we ordered half cup of beer and she brought a cup. And we said it's not what we ordered and she didn't change for us... amazing for this unfair deal.
Very nice place to have a beer and enjoy the great food. There is an old fashioned dance club on the lower floor 🙃
Great beer, and ambience. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Great place to enjoy your afternoon
Service was prime! Food was served very fast. Our waiter Peter was extremely kind.

Quite a nice Bavarian brewhouse restaurant. The welcome and staff were super nice and fun, fast, too. The food was very well done, loved the Schnitzel, the Spatzle and everything else.

Great atmosphere too....will for sure be back soon.

name: Leo`s Lounge Restaurant Happy Hour Cocktailbar München
description: Gemütliches Brunchlokal & Bar mit traditioneller Dekoration, internationaler Küche und Sport im TV.

reviews.comment: Don’t expect a classic German beer house. They have a lot of different food. I am not sure if it is a good thing.
Nice bar for cocktails. I did not try the food.
Very nice restaurant, great people, great service and very friendly staff 😀
The Tex Mex stuff is great. Drinks are tasty, and generous.

The place was really nice and food is also very tasty, specially the fajitas.
A little bit disappointed with the cocktails.. But i think thats okay.

name: YUM thai kitchen & bar
description: Thairestaurant mit traditionellem Edeldekor, in dem klassische Gerichte serviert werden, mit Cocktailkarte.

reviews.comment:
A beautiful looking restaurant and dining experience. There is a cute little bar just inside here for some basic cocktails.

The food is tasty and pretty close to traditional. Its a little on the mild side when it comes to spice.

The prices are on the higher side so be prepared to spend when you sit down here. The prices also apply for a takeaway for two.

Excellent and authentic Thai cuisine.  As a tourist. A great break from the (still fantastic) Bavarian food we have has the last week.
Good variants I don’t have else elsewhere though.  Good mix with duck and all the food washes down with great local beer.
The waiter took pity on us and gave us their home made chilli sauce.  Mixing it in and I immediately added 3 more stars to their already 5 star rating.

The food and atmosphere are excellent. My family and I had a great experience and we will definitely come back. The papaya salad with the fermented fish sauce reminded me my trip to north Thailand 20 years ago.
An upscale place. I would rate it as $$$ rather than $$. A bit too pricey and Almost too fancy for a dinner out. Perfect for a special occasion. Outstanding food and service.

Top quality service. Very nice environment.
The food was very tasteful, one of the best thai i’ve ever tried!

name: Gaststätte Lucullus
description: Traditionelle griechische Gerichte in einem zwanglosen, freundlich eingerichteten Restaurant mit Terrasse.

reviews.comment: Very pleasant casual neighborhood Greek restaurant. Fast and friendly service, generous portion sizes, inexpensive. We came early, sat at an outdoor table. Restaurant is very busy, recommend a reservation. Food is very good, although nothing unusual/spectacular.

Amazing atmosphere in the beergarden outside! The food is authentic and tastes amazing, as expected. The staff is very polite, helpful and pay attention to all the little details to make the customers happy. The prices are fair for the portions you get. I loved being there and will definitely go again :) 10/10 recommend
Excellent food, massive portions, affordable prices, friendly and willing staff.  Well done!
Great Greek food, lovely location, good prices and excellent customer service!  Have come several times with several groups of people, and it's always been a great time!

This is a wonderfully authentic Greek restaurant offering the perfect escape from Munich while within Munich. Big portions at very reasonable prices, friendly staff, all with a charming slice of southern European chaos. I can only roll my eyes at some of whingeing in these reviews - if you want complete predictability and precision in your dining experience, perhaps you should stick to eating at your local Wirtshaus.

name: China Restaurant Global Wok
description: Das Restaurant mit Holzschnitzereien serviert asiatische Spezialitäten auch vom Buffet und mongolischen Grill.

reviews.comment: We went there on Sunday 11:30am, it’s nice place, there’s free parking, the restaurant is spacious, the sit is comfortable, the food is taste good, fresh and the staff were friendly, approachable and polite. It’s just more pricey compare to other. But overall we had a good time.
Super Service
Great place and food. If you are a beginner in Chinese food tradition, is hard to find a good advise in any other language than German.

Overall spacious and clean interior. What i didnt like was the use of too much salt in most dishes, and also for the grilled foods. Some dishes are ok and reasonably seasoned. But overall i just remember the saltiness :(.
What do you favorite sushi? If you like sushi you can come here global wok restaurant.very good foods with Salat and fresh fruits and all you can drink and eat very good prices thanks everybody.

name: Farmers Steakhouse
description: Burger und Steaks von argentinischen Rindern im rot gestrichenen Lokal oder auf der Sonnenterrasse.

reviews.comment: Great spot for a business lunch in Garching. Quick and friendly service. Offers safe and calm outdoor seating.
Extremely good food. Very nice drinks. Amazing waitress.

The burger was overcooked. It took more than an hour until our food was ready (6 people). The steak was ok, but overpriced for the size. Also the fact that you need to pay extra for the sauce is a negative point. The waitress was friendly and the restaurant has a nice atmosphere.

The food is very good, but getting more and more expensive over the years. It's become a bit pricey now...
The atmosphere of the restaurant is very nice and clean, especially nice to sit outside in the summer!
Only downside is the at best neutral at worst down right unfriendly and sometimes even arrogant wait staff.

Nice place, the staff is friendly and the food is good. The soup is usually served way too hot (be very careful not to burn yourself!) and the vegetarian burger is a bit boring (meat replaced with off the shelf breaded oven cheese).

name: La Pergola cucina italiana
description: Das rustikale Lokal mit bordeauxfarbenem Interieur serviert italienische Speisen und hausgemachte Pasta.

reviews.comment:
Authentic Italian cousine.
I only tried the pizzas, and I have to say, they were top quality. From the dough to the sauce, heavenly made.
At the back of the menu there is a list of allergens, that will allow vegans, vegetarians, celiacs, etc, to find options suitable for them (its an okay system, although a label next to the plate or a vegan/vegetarian section in the menu would probably be more efficient).

The ambience is nice and the service is ok. They also sell some import products from Italy, such as sauces and drinks.

Great place to go to and very central if you a visiting Garching.
My fave pizza from Garching. Also great tiramisu

Good food and reasonable prices. Not overly expensive, especially when compared to other places in Garching. The only sore point I've got to mention is the staff, wouldn't hurt them to be a bit friendlier and more welcoming.

Delivery from this place works quite well and combined with the good food is a very viable alternative.
Great authentic food
The Best team

name: RAMA Ismaning
description: Das indische Lokal serviert auch italienische Speisen und verbindet orientalisches und gutbürgerliches Dekor.

reviews.comment: Loved the food and really nice outdoor seating. I had the veg thali which is very filling for one person.
Went to get take out here many times, the food and the quality was amazing.
Whenever we visit our home town in Bavaria, we go here at least once. The food here is great, especially if you like it spicy.

I can only review their midday menu, haven't been in the evening. Terrace is great in summer, lunch service is snappy and a lamb rogan josh, rice, naan and a lassi came to €20, which is reasonable. Food is spicy (if it says it's spicy, it will be!)

Food is awesome can give ir a chance
When you start frequently going and ordering food home the quantity and quality depreciates oil increase food decrease and when u go in starting its good experience but when you keep going again and again or order for carrying their services and food quality gets worst

name: Bakeries Ludwig Riedmair
description: Traditionelle Backwaren & Cafe

reviews.comment:
Lovely breakfast. Good quality of breads and rolls. Did not taste sweets.
Good range of tea and the fresh made orange juice is great.
I was here today. Sweet bakery was a very delicious and workers were friendly.
Very good bread, cake and hamburger buns on Fridays 🙂
Friendly and helpful

Over many years we have gone to the same bakery - until we discover Riedmaier in Munich.

I’m blown away by the excellent bretzel they have and the breakfast for two is just fantastic- fresh quality - keep up the great work!! And you will have lots of customers

name: Nano Sushi
description: Japanisches Restaurant mit Sushi, Ramen-Nudelsuppen, Udon- und Soba-Nudeln und Online-Bestellung.

reviews.comment: Excellent sushi. Pleasant quiet place, great service, great food. Perhaps a bit pricey, but you understand what you are paying for. Will visit again.
Good sushi restaurant with also other Japanese dishes. The sushi is of good quality with a good quality/price ration.

Omg THIS IS THE BEST SUSHI EVER!!! The quality is INCREDIBLY HIGH!! I've eaten at almost every sushi place in Munich and this is hands down the best. I forgot sushi could be like this...
The owner told me that he only uses the very best quality ingredients, even if that makes it harder on them to make a profit.
Btw they have hot dishes as well and the Ramen is out of this world!!
The atmosphere is also really cute. Great date night or place with friends and also a nice outside area with umbrellas. If I could give 10 stars, I would!
Very well prepared, took little time, and the waiter was very nice. Would go again.
Large selection of great sushi

name: Freiraum
description: Modernes Kantinen-Restaurant auf Business Campus mit internationalen Gerichten, Selbstbedienung und Terrasse.

reviews.comment: Food Quality is okay, not price worthy
Nice place to grab lunch while at work
There are always option for vegetarian. Fish items, time to time, are also delicious.

Nice business restaurant with a good view outside. I like the variety of food offered everyday. There is always a choice of meat based meals  and vegetarian options. Variety of salads and soups are also offered. The only negative points is opening hours, sometimes I reach at 1:45 pm or 2:00 pm and the place is already closed. Would be nice if the place can offer few dishes after 2 pm or some light snacks.
Good choice for lunch.

name: LA PERLA Cucina Bar Pizzeria
description: Traditionelle italienische Gerichte in einer kleinen, modernen und kreativen Atmosphäre.

reviews.comment: Lasagne is so bad full of sauce.the taste was just  sauce.noting else.i didn't like it .
Great food and service!
very nice Italy food! very good service
Clean and kind peoples
very good！nice people，will come again！

name: Cafe Herr Lichtenberg
description: Kleines und charmantes Cafe am Campus Garching

reviews.comment: This place is amazing. They have 2 permanent dishes in the menu: A falafel salad and a burger, and 3 other dishes they change every day, usually different pastas, meats or fish. The burger buns are homemade, the brownies are homemade, and let me tell you, they taste incredible. The prices are very reasonable, given that most of the food is homemade and the portions are quite big (for instance, the burger is 7.20 euros). 10/10, would recommend.

Tasty hipster place with affordable prices.
They offer baked goods as well as fully fledged lunch meals.
Plenty of outside seating for coronatimes.
Good
Nice lunch menu, love their soups, except their one fruit soup which they try every week. Otherwise healthy and decent food.
The staff is always extremely friendly, and the food is consistently good. It’s also great vibes all around and a really relaxing atmosphere 👌 I honestly love this cafe.

name: UNO Pizzeria Ismaning
description: Traditionelle italienische Gerichte in einer urigen Atmosphäre am Rande Münchens

reviews.comment: The food is very very tasty. Quick and fresh pizza with a very good Fragrance and Melting Cheese in mouth.. super tasty must visit and try.. Even Delivery also so quick good service..!!
The pizza is excellent and great value. They have good beers, and a good selection of drinks. The guys in the pizzaria are really cool as well. I definitely recommend this place for take away pizza!
Loved it
I love this place. Great pizza, cheap beer, and its close to the residential area I live in.
Love the taste of pizza,pasta and also indian food.Customer friendly approach. Quick service.
